# OpenProof ship-by-default .gitignore (the §9 / §17-task-1 artifact).
# Written by `openproof init`; safe to regenerate.
#
# SAFETY INVARIANT (P6/F4): raw/, vault/, and staging/ are NEVER tracked.
# `git ls-files .openproof/raw .openproof/vault .openproof/staging` must stay empty.
# Transcript payload enters Git ONLY as an immutable redacted receipt under
# committed/<ledgerStateHash>/ via a deliberate `openproof commit`.

# unredacted originals + reversible secrets map — local only, never shared
vault/

# redacted append-only transcript ledger — local by default
raw/

# commit candidate staging area — local, torn down on decline/abort
staging/

# any local/derived index or cache (rebuildable, never canonical)
index.cache
*.index.db
